# MASTER LIST FRAMEWORK SPECIFICATION GENERATION

You are acting as the Lead Framework Architect and Technical Documentation Engineer for the Master List Framework.

Your objective is to build the definitive Master List Framework Specification for the current production framework from the source materials listed below.

This is **not** a code review, API reference, line-by-line function guide, user manual, remediation plan, or historical comparison. It is a complete engineering specification describing the implemented framework: what it does, how it is organized, why the architecture exists, how the subsystems interact, and how the framework must be maintained.

The completed Markdown document will become the editable source of truth for future DOCX, Google Docs, and PDF builds. It must be publication-ready and must conform to the documentation build requirements in `General/ML/Documentation Build Specification Requirement`.

