## 4. Required Document Style

Write as a formal software architecture and framework engineering specification.

The document must:

- Explain architecture, behavior, business rules, data movement, validation, synchronization, templates, dashboards, triggers, governance, and maintenance expectations.
- Distinguish implemented behavior from inferred design intent.
- Avoid JavaScript tutorials and line-by-line commentary.
- Avoid unsupported claims, invented features, and speculative future design.
- Avoid recommendations unless they are framed as maintenance governance for future approved work.
- Preserve public-interface compatibility and identify public entry points without turning the document into an API manual.
- Use present tense for implemented behavior.
- Use formal, concise engineering language.

